org.jcvi.jillion.assembly.consed.ace

Interface AceFileVisitor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAceFileVisitor, MultiAceFileVisitorAdapter

    public interface AceFileVisitor
    AceFileVisitor is a Visitor implementation for .ace encoded assembly files.

    The AceFileVisitor will have the appropriate visit methods called on it as an ace file is parsed/ traversed.

    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Detail

      • visitHeader

        void visitHeader(int numberOfContigs,
                 long totalNumberOfReads)
        Visits the Ace File Header.
        Parameters:
        numberOfContigs - number of contigs in this file.
        totalNumberOfReads - total number of reads in this file.

      • visitContig

        AceContigVisitor visitContig(AceFileVisitorCallback callback,
                             String contigId,
                             int numberOfBases,
                             int numberOfReads,
                             int numberOfBaseSegments,
                             boolean reverseComplemented)
        Denotes when a new contig has been detected.
        Parameters:
        callback - an AceFileVisitorCallback instance.
        contigId - the id of the contig visited.
        numberOfBases - number of bases in contig (Does this count bases outside of valid range?)
        numberOfReads - number of reads in contig.
        numberOfBaseSegments - number of base segment lines which indicate reads phrap has chosen to be the consensus at a particular position.
        reverseComplemented - is this contig reverse complemented
        Returns:
        an instance of AceContigVisitor which will get its visitXXX methods called for this particular contig; or null if this contig should be skipped.

      • visitReadTag

        void visitReadTag(String id,
                  String type,
                  String creator,
                  long gappedStart,
                  long gappedEnd,
                  Date creationDate,
                  boolean isTransient)
        Visit a tag that refers to data concerning a single read in the assembly.
        Parameters:
        id - the read id.
        type - the type of this tag; will not have any whitespace.
        creator - the program or tool that generated this tag.
        gappedStart - the gapped start offset where this tag refers. Depending on what the tag is used for this could be consensus coordinates or read coordinates.
        gappedEnd - the gapped end offset where this tag refers. Depending on what the tag is used for this could be consensus coordinates or read coordinates.
        creationDate - the date that this tag was created.
        isTransient - a transient tag should not be preserved if the assembly is re-assembled; returns true if transient; false otherwise.

      • visitConsensusTag

        AceConsensusTagVisitor visitConsensusTag(String id,
                                         String type,
                                         String creator,
                                         long gappedStart,
                                         long gappedEnd,
                                         Date creationDate,
                                         boolean isTransient)
        Begin to start visiting a consensus tag. Consensus tags are multiple lines and can contain nested comments inside them. Any lines visited from now until visitEnd() will be for lines inside this tag.
        Parameters:
        id - the contig id.
        type - the type of this tag; will not have any whitespace.
        creator - the program or tool that generated this tag.
        gappedStart - the gapped start offset where this tag refers. Depending on what the tag is used for this could be consensus coordinates or read coordinates.
        gappedEnd - the gapped end offset where this tag refers. Depending on what the tag is used for this could be consensus coordinates or read coordinates.
        creationDate - the date that this tag was created.
        isTransient - a transient tag should not be preserved if the assembly is re-assembled; returns true if transient; false otherwise.
        Returns:
        a AceConsensusTagVisitor to be visited; or null if this tag should be skipped.

      • visitWholeAssemblyTag

        void visitWholeAssemblyTag(String type,
                           String creator,
                           Date creationDate,
                           String data)
        Visit a tag that refers to data that concerns the entire ace file. Example whole assembly tags are locations to phd.balls that store the quality data for all the reads in the assembly.
        Parameters:
        type - the type of this tag; will not have any whitespace.
        creator - the program or tool that generated this tag.
        creationDate - the date that this tag was created.
        data - the actual content of this tag which could be a single line or span multiple lines depending on what the tag is for.
